reviewText: Okay, the premise really is strange - that is all I will say but it is well done and works.  A combination of romance juxtaposed within society's constraint that no one is really happy unless they are married.

reviewText: The premise was good and it started out really well.  She was determined to make people realise that she didn't need a man to make her life complete.  Enter the man and she turned into one of the women she was trying not to be.  I didn't like that she didn't tell the guy about her decision to marry herself and his reaction was predictable.  There are so many ways this movie should have gone but it didn't do it for me.  It's a shame because it had so many possibilities.

reviewText: This movie is irrestible!  I have watched it over and over and I enjoy it more each time I watch it.  When Isabel fell in love, it was head over heels, just when she least expected it.  The best things in life happen when you don't look for them.  Colin was a perfect match.  Everyone in real life should be as lucky as they were.
